      • nationAdd

        public void nationAdd(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                      String[] names)
               throws TownyException
        First stage of adding towns to a nation. Tests here are performed to make sure Nation is allowed to add the towns: - make sure the nation hasn't already hit the max towns (if that is required in teh config.)
        Parameters:
        player - - Player using the command.
        names - - Names that will be matched to towns.
        Throws:
        TownyException - generic

      • nationAdd

        public static void nationAdd(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                             Nation nation,
                             List<Town> invited)
                      throws TownyException
        Second stage of adding towns to a nation. Tests here are performed to make sure the Towns are allowed to join the Nation: - make sure the town has enough residents to join a nation (if it is required in the config.) - make sure the town is close enough to the nation capital (if it is required in the config.) Lastly, invites are sent and if successful, the third stage is called by the invite handler.
        Parameters:
        player - player sending the request
        nation - Nation sending the request
        invited - the Town(s) being invited to the Nation
        Throws:
        TownyException - executed when the arraylist (invited) returns empty (no valid town was entered)
